The federal government plans to produce 12 million bags of NPK fertiliser for sale to farmers at subsidised rates for the 2020 farming season. The chairman, Presidential Fertiliser Initiative Committee, Governor Muhammad Abubakar Badaru of Jigawa State, disclosed this to newsmen who he briefed on the committee’s preparation for the supply of the fertiliser amidst COVID-19 pandemic.He said that the committee has already imported enough Phosphate and Potash while Urea and Fillers are to be sourced locally for the production of the fertiliser. The committee chairman noted that, 29 Fertiliser Blending Companies across 13 states of the federation were given mandate for the production of the fertiliser. Badaru explained that President Muhammad Buhari directed further subsidies in the price of the NPK fertiliser, and that a bag is to be sold at the cost of N5,000  instead of N5,500. The governor added that the reduction of the price is part of President Buhari’s palliative measures against coronavirus pandemic to encourage farmers to produce more farm produce to ensure food security in the country. He explained that the new price is with immediate effect.